description:
People really hate the phrase "Diversity Is Our Strength" and this video looks into the whys of that. I also take a moment to look at how the phrase became popular, and who the people popularizing it are.

Fun fact: This video was originally over 40 minutes long, and was originally only supposed to be 15.

You can follow me on the Twitter:  https://twitter.com/JoseNotAJay

My Patreon: https://www.patreon.com/JoseOnYoutube

Sources for this video:

Media Matters clip: https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=-YjHgYg025s

Wemple article: https://www.washingtonpost.com/blogs/erik-wemple/wp/2018/09/10/face-it-tucker-carlson-your-anti-diversity-segment-was-racist/?utm_term=.efb3639093e0

Red Ice video: https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=3w48P6sYJ6o

NPR Putnam interview: https://www.npr.org/templates/story/story.php?storyId=12802663

Harvard Business Review article: https://hbr.org/2016/07/why-diversity-programs-fail

Third Red Ice Video: https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=nYag1lOZpLw

Red Elephants Video: https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=TcWYAa4Y2C0
